arch:property.oc:show_val: Munsell 7.5 YR 4/4 (Brown). Layer of loose, silty topsoils, modern and early modern deposits, and materials washed downhill from the Lower Temenos area. In general, the locus is of limited stratigraphic and interpretive value.
Phase XII: Robbing and abandonment continue.
Phase XIV: Modern period marked by Bedouin activity and the accumulation of recent debris.
Closing elevation: 893.848 m in west, 894.019 m in east.
Opening elevation: 895.622 m in north, 895.012 m in south.
Phase XIII: Major collapses continue into the Islamic period.
